<emphasis box="[1025,1100,1036,1062]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">Belyta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of the following characters: macropterous, notauli present, mandibles of ordinary form, scutellum without a row of foveae along posterior margin, marginal vein shorter than its distance from basal vein, pronotum elongate, without a hollow on each side (= pronotal pits), epomia present, median keel of propodeum simple, petiole more than one and a half time as long as wide. The flattened body is generally accepted to diagnose 
<taxonomicName box="[299,428,1212,1238]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Belyta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[299,374,1212,1238]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">Belyta</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Macek J." box="[441,588,1212,1239]" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" pagination="29 - 39" refId="ref15400" refString="Macek J. 1996. Revision of the European species of Belyta Jurine. Acta Musei Nationalis Prague, Series B, Historia Naturalis 51 (1 - 4): 29 - 39." type="journal article" year="1996">Macek 1996</bibRefCitation>
) and is present in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" box="[792,1059,1212,1238]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Belyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="knudhoejgaardi">
<emphasis box="[792,1059,1212,1238]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">Belyta knudhoejgaardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, strengthening the placement of the species in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jurine" authorityYear="1807" box="[386,461,1247,1273]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Belyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[386,461,1247,1273]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">Belyta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,1399,1312,1550]" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">
Following the key to European species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jurine" authorityYear="1807" box="[681,756,1312,1338]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Belyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[681,756,1312,1338]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">Belyta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of 
<bibRefCitation author="Macek J." box="[795,963,1312,1339]" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" pagination="29 - 39" refId="ref15400" refString="Macek J. 1996. Revision of the European species of Belyta Jurine. Acta Musei Nationalis Prague, Series B, Historia Naturalis 51 (1 - 4): 29 - 39." type="journal article" year="1996">Macek (1996)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen, 2022" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" box="[974,1241,1312,1338]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Belyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="knudhoejgaardi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[974,1241,1312,1338]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">Belyta knudhoejgaardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1248,1338,1313,1339]" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
keys out between 
<taxonomicName authority="Kieffer, 1916" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1916" box="[341,657,1348,1374]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Belyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subclausa">
<emphasis box="[341,491,1348,1374]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">B. subclausa</emphasis>
Kieffer, 1916
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Thomson, 1858" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1858" box="[716,1084,1347,1374]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Belyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="validicornis">
<emphasis box="[716,889,1348,1374]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">B. validicornis</emphasis>
Thomson, 1858
</taxonomicName>
. It differs from the first by having a marked epomia and from the second by having the median propodeal keel simple (
<bibRefCitation author="Macek J." pageId="5" pageNumber="62" pagination="29 - 39" refId="ref15400" refString="Macek J. 1996. Revision of the European species of Belyta Jurine. Acta Musei Nationalis Prague, Series B, Historia Naturalis 51 (1 - 4): 29 - 39." type="journal article" year="1996">Macek 1996</bibRefCitation>
). The diagnostic character for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" box="[608,875,1418,1444]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Belyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="knudhoejgaardi">
<emphasis box="[608,875,1418,1444]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">Belyta knudhoejgaardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the curiously marked longitudinal keel on the mesopleuron, which is absent in other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jurine" authorityYear="1807" box="[828,901,1453,1479]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Belyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[828,901,1453,1479]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">Belyta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. From the Eocene of Florissant is known 
<taxonomicName authority="Brues, 1910" authorityName="Brues" authorityYear="1910" box="[191,490,1488,1515]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Belyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mortuella">
<emphasis box="[191,339,1488,1514]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">B. mortuella</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Brues C. T." box="[346,490,1489,1515]" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" pagination="3 - 125" refId="ref13960" refString="Brues C. T. 1910. The parasitic Hymenoptera of the Tertiary of Florissant, Colorado. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, Harvard College 54 (1): 3 - 125. Available from https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 30208802 [accessed 2 Jan. 2021]." type="journal article" year="1910">Brues, 1910</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(attributed to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jurine" authorityYear="1807" box="[663,738,1488,1514]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Belyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="lato">
<emphasis box="[663,738,1488,1514]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">Belyta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[745,812,1488,1515]" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" sensu="lato">s. lat.</taxonomicNameLabel>
), which differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" box="[1069,1288,1488,1514]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Belyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="knudhoejgaardi">
<emphasis box="[1069,1288,1488,1514]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">B. knudhoejgaardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by being shorter and having a less flattened body (
<bibRefCitation author="Brues C. T." box="[670,811,1524,1550]" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" pagination="3 - 125" refId="ref13960" refString="Brues C. T. 1910. The parasitic Hymenoptera of the Tertiary of Florissant, Colorado. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, Harvard College 54 (1): 3 - 125. Available from https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 30208802 [accessed 2 Jan. 2021]." type="journal article" year="1910">Brues 1910</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
